commit.message:
Add firmware_info structure.

Co-authored-by: Mike Walters <mike@flomp.net>
Detect HackRF hardware revision.
Add support for HackRF r9.
Remove obsolete and commented out asserts.

Remove duplicated initial SCU configurations.

The init() method on Pin was never called, and the configuration data
stored in _initial_config was never used. The initial SCU settings that
are actually used at startup are the ones in pal_default_config.
Use abstract MAX283x interface wherever possible.
Add MAX283x abstract base class.
Add MAX2839 driver.
HackRF: Update for HackRF One r9 support.
Track mixer and baseband inversion separately.

Perform full peripheral reset for HackRF mode.

When exiting PortaPack and passing total control to alternative firmware
it can be helpful to restore the reset state as much as possible. The
peripheral reset includes both the M4 and M0, but the M0 is not
immediately reset as it requires an additional register write.
Restrict IF to 2170-2740 MHz.

Clock Manager: Store correct crystal frequency.

This corrects the frequency displayed in Setup.
Convince GCC 10 to use compile-time array length.
